An avalanche swept through an area near Entraunes in the French Alps on Friday, killing at least four people, police said in a statement. One person was taken to hospital with injuries, while the group's guide escaped unharmed. Another individual is still unaccounted for. The group was reportedly skiing off-piste in a remote part of the Mercantour National Park when the avalanche struck just after midday. Prime Minister Edouard Philippe told reporters that a rescue operation was underway. Read more: Our beautiful planet: Snow across Europe "These valleys are highly popular with off-piste skiers because it's beautiful and wild," said Christophe Ollivier, a local official in nearby Vesubie. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
